The Longitudinal Early-onset Alzheimer's Disease Study (LEADS) is a non-randomized, natural history, non-treatment study designed to look at disease progression in individuals with early onset Alzheimer's disease (EOAD).

 Clinical/cognitive, imaging, biomarker, and genetic characteristics will be assessed across two cohorts: (1) individuals with EOAD and (2) cognitively normal (CN) control participants.

